datasets.name: 0e271bac
datasets.query:
-- return state for all jobs for last 14 days
with job_runs as (
    select job_id
        ,from_utc_timestamp(period_start_time,'CET') as start_time_cet
        ,from_utc_timestamp(period_end_time,'CET') as end_time_cet
        ,to_date(from_utc_timestamp(period_start_time,'CET')) as start_date
        ,trigger_type
        ,result_state
from system.lakeflow.job_run_timeline
where to_date(period_start_time) >= to_date(from_utc_timestamp(current_timestamp(),'CET'))-INTERVAL 30 DAY 
), jobs as (
    select job_id       
        ,name as job_name
        ,tags
        ,creator_id
        ,run_as
from system.lakeflow.jobs
)select j.job_id
        ,j.job_name
        ,jr.start_date
        ,jr.start_time_cet
        ,result_state
from job_runs jr left join jobs j on jr.job_id = j.job_id

datasets.name: b7322e2a
datasets.query:
with job_runs as (
    select job_id
        ,from_utc_timestamp(period_start_time,'CET') as start_time_cet
        ,from_utc_timestamp(period_end_time,'CET') as end_time_cet
        ,to_date(from_utc_timestamp(period_start_time,'CET')) as start_date
        ,trigger_type
        ,result_state
from system.lakeflow.job_run_timeline
where to_date(period_start_time) >= to_date(from_utc_timestamp(current_timestamp(),'CET'))-INTERVAL 30 DAY 
), jobs as (
    select job_id       
        ,name as job_name
        ,tags
        ,creator_id
        ,run_as
from system.lakeflow.jobs
),prefin as (
    select j.job_id
        ,j.job_name
        ,jr.start_date
        ,jr.start_time_cet
        ,result_state
from job_runs jr left join jobs j on jr.job_id = j.job_id
)
select start_date
    ,round(count_if(result_state = 'SUCCEEDED')/count(*),3) as suc_ratio 
    ,round(count_if(result_state = 'ERROR')/count(*),3) as error_ratio 
    ,round(count_if(result_state = 'SKIPPED')/count(*),3) as skip_ratio 
    ,round(count_if(result_state = 'CANCELED')/count(*),3) as cancel_ratio 
from prefin group by all

datasets.name: ad29428c
datasets.query:
with list_cost_per_job_run as (
  select u.workspace_id,
        u.usage_metadata.job_id,
        u.usage_metadata.job_run_id as run_id,
        SUM(u.usage_quantity * lp.pricing.default) as list_cost, -- new option for promo price
        first(identity_metadata.run_as, true) as run_as,
        first(u.custom_tags, true) as custom_tags,
        MAX(from_utc_timestamp(u.usage_end_time,'CET')) as last_seen_date -- because price/usage is calculated after finish job
  from system.billing.usage u 
  inner join system.billing.list_prices lp on
    u.cloud = lp.cloud and
    u.sku_name = lp.sku_name and
    u.usage_start_time >= lp.price_start_time and
    (u.usage_end_time <= lp.price_end_time or lp.price_end_time is null)
  where u.usage_metadata.job_id is not NULL
    and u.usage_metadata.job_run_id is not NULL
    and u.usage_date >= CURRENT_DATE() - INTERVAL 30 DAY 
  group by all
),

most_recent_jobs as (
  select *, 
        row_number() over(partition by workspace_id, job_id order by change_time desc) as rn
  from system.lakeflow.jobs 
  qualify rn=1
)
select 
    t1.workspace_id,
    t2.name as job_name,
    to_date(t1.last_seen_date) as usage_date,
    t1.job_id,
    t1.run_id,
     t1.run_as,
    SUM(list_cost) as job_price_usd
FROM list_cost_per_job_run t1 
  LEFT JOIN most_recent_jobs t2 USING (workspace_id, job_id)
GROUP BY ALL

datasets.name: 5697f865
datasets.query:
-- most expensive jobs for last 30d, cumulative price and cnt runs per period
-- fetch first 15 rows - that is enough
-- null in job_name mean that we have no job_name - must investigate
with list_cost_per_job_run as (
  select u.workspace_id,
        u.usage_metadata.job_id,
        SUM(u.usage_quantity * lp.pricing.default) as list_cost, -- new option for promo price
        first(identity_metadata.run_as, true) as run_as,
        first(u.custom_tags, true) as custom_tags,
        MAX(from_utc_timestamp(u.usage_end_time,'CET')) as last_seen_date, -- because price/usage is calculated after finish job
        COUNT(DISTINCT u.usage_metadata.job_run_id) as runs -- cnt runs of single job
  from system.billing.usage u 
  inner join system.billing.list_prices lp on
    u.cloud = lp.cloud and
    u.sku_name = lp.sku_name and
    u.usage_start_time >= lp.price_start_time and
    (u.usage_end_time <= lp.price_end_time or lp.price_end_time is null)
  where u.usage_metadata.job_id is not NULL
    and u.usage_metadata.job_run_id is not NULL
    and u.usage_date >= CURRENT_DATE() - INTERVAL 30 DAY 
  group by all
),
most_recent_jobs as (
  select *, 
        row_number() over(partition by workspace_id, job_id order by change_time desc) as rn
  from system.lakeflow.jobs 
  qualify rn=1
)
select 
    lc.workspace_id
    ,mcj.name as job_name
    ,lc.job_id
    ,lc.run_as
    ,SUM(lc.list_cost) as job_price_usd
    ,lc.runs
FROM list_cost_per_job_run lc 
  LEFT JOIN most_recent_jobs mcj USING (workspace_id, job_id)
GROUP BY ALL
order by job_price_usd desc
limit 15

with jn as (

        ,run_id
        ,from_utc_timestamp(period_start_time,'CET') as start_time_cet

        ,j.*
from jd j left join jn n on j.job_id = n.job_id

datasets.name: eac14418
datasets.query:
with job_run_timeline_with_cost as (
  select
    u.*,
    u.usage_metadata.job_id as job_id,
    u.identity_metadata.run_as as run_as,
    u.usage_quantity * lp.pricing.default as list_cost
  from system.billing.usage u
    inner join system.billing.list_prices lp on u.cloud = lp.cloud
    and u.sku_name = lp.sku_name
    and u.usage_start_time >= lp.price_start_time
    and (
      u.usage_end_time <= lp.price_end_time
      or lp.price_end_time is NULL
    )
  where
    u.sku_name like '%JOBS%' -- only job clusters
    and u.usage_metadata.job_id is not NULL
    and u.usage_metadata.job_run_id is not NULL
    and u.usage_date >= CURRENT_DATE() - INTERVAL 14 DAY
),
most_recent_jobs as (-- only actual setup of jobs
  select
    *,
    ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY workspace_id,job_id ORDER BY change_time DESC) as rn
  from
    system.lakeflow.jobs qualify rn = 1
)
SELECT
  t2.name,
  t1.workspace_id,
  t1.job_id,
  t1.sku_name,
  t1.run_as,
  spend_last_0_7_days,
  spend_last_8_14_days,
  spend_last_0_7_days - spend_last_8_14_days as last_0_7d_cost_growth,
  try_divide(
    (spend_last_0_7_days - spend_last_8_14_days),
    spend_last_8_14_days
  ) * 100 AS last_0_7_d_growth_pct -- how many % growth cost compare last week/two weeks ago
FROM
  (
    SELECT
      workspace_id,
      job_id,
      run_as,
      sku_name,
      SUM(list_cost) AS spend,
      SUM(
        CASE 
          WHEN usage_end_time BETWEEN date_add(current_date(), -8) AND date_add(current_date(), -1) THEN list_cost 
          ELSE 0
        END
      ) AS spend_last_0_7_days,
      SUM(
        CASE
          WHEN usage_end_time BETWEEN date_add(current_date(), -15) AND date_add(current_date(), -8) THEN list_cost
          ELSE 0
        END
      ) AS spend_last_8_14_days
    FROM
      job_run_timeline_with_cost
    GROUP BY
      ALL
  ) t1
  LEFT JOIN most_recent_jobs t2 USING (workspace_id, job_id)
ORDER BY
  last_0_7d_cost_growth DESC
LIMIT
  100

datasets.name: e0e2a9a1
datasets.query:
with clusters AS (
  SELECT
    *,
    ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY workspace_id, cluster_id ORDER BY change_time DESC) as rn
  FROM system.compute.clusters
  WHERE cluster_source="UI" -- all purpose
  QUALIFY rn=1
),
job_tasks_exploded AS (
  SELECT
    workspace_id,
    job_id,
    EXPLODE(compute_ids) as cluster_id
  FROM system.lakeflow.job_task_run_timeline
  WHERE period_start_time >= CURRENT_DATE() - INTERVAL 30 DAY 
),
all_purpose_cluster_jobs AS (
  SELECT
    t1.*,
    t2.cluster_name,
    t2.owned_by,
    t2.dbr_version
  FROM job_tasks_exploded t1 
    INNER JOIN clusters t2 USING (workspace_id, cluster_id)
),
most_recent_jobs as (
  SELECT 
    *, 
    ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY workspace_id, job_id ORDER BY change_time DESC) as rn
  FROM
    system.lakeflow.jobs QUALIFY rn=1
)
SELECT 
  t1.workspace_id,
  t1.job_id,
  first(t2.name, TRUE) as name,
  array_size(collect_list(t1.cluster_id)) as task_runs,
  collect_set(
    named_struct(
      'cluster_id', t1.cluster_id,
      'cluster_name', t1.cluster_name
    )
  ) as clusters_list
FROM all_purpose_cluster_jobs t1 
  LEFT JOIN most_recent_jobs t2 USING (workspace_id, job_id)
GROUP BY t1.workspace_id, t1.job_id 
ORDER BY task_runs DESC
LIMIT 100;
